---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const pageTitle = 'Privacy Policy'
const description = 'Tiny Tides Therapy, Baltimore Pediatric Occupational Therapy - Privacy Policy'
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} description={description}>
    <div class="w-full pt-14 sm:pt-[76px] flex justify-center">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
            <main class="px-6 py-8 text-gray-800 flex flex-col gap-y-4">
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal-600 mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: October 8, 2025</p>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">Introduction</h2>
                    <p>
                    Welcome to <strong>Tiny Tides Therapy</strong> (“we,” “our,” or “us”). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect,
                    use, disclose, and protect information when you visit
                    <a href="https://www.tinytidestherapy.com" class="text-teal-600 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">our website</a>
                    (the “Site”). By using the Site, you accept the practices described in this policy.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">1. Information We Collect</h2>
                    <p class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Voluntary information:</strong> We only collect personal information that you voluntarily provide through
                    forms on the Site. This may include:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-3 space-y-1">
                    <li>Name</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>Phone number</li>
                    <li>Any other information you include in a message or form submission</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="mb-3">
                    <strong>Automatically collected information:</strong> We use Google Analytics and similar tools to collect
                    limited, non-identifying technical data (like pages visited, referral source, and browser type) to help us
                    improve the Site.
                    </p>
                    <div class="bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> The Site does not collect personal information unless you submit a form.
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-3 space-y-1">
                    <li>To respond to your inquiries or requests submitted via the Site</li>
                    <li>To schedule or manage therapy services when applicable</li>
                    <li>To process payments if you make a payment through the Site</li>
                    <li>To send you information you’ve requested (such as appointment confirmations)</li>
                    <li>To analyze and improve our website and services</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>We will not sell or rent your personal information to third parties.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">3. Third-Party Services</h2>
                    <p class="mb-3">We use a small set of trusted third-party services to operate and improve the Site:</p>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-3 space-y-1">
                    <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — for website traffic and usage analytics</li>
                    <li><strong>Email service providers</strong> (Mailchimp, Resend, etc.) — to send emails</li>
                    <li><strong>Payment processors</strong> (Stripe, PayPal, etc.) — to securely process payments</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Each provider has its own privacy policy and practices. We encourage you to review those directly.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                    <p>
                    We may use cookies and similar technologies for analytics, to remember preferences, and to improve your
                    experience. You can control cookies in your browser settings, though disabling them may affect certain features.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">5. Data Retention</h2>
                    <p>
                    We retain personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose for which it was collected, to
                    comply with legal obligations, or to resolve disputes.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">6. Data Security</h2>
                    <p>
                    We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your information. However, no
                    method of transmission or storage is 100% secure. We cannot guarantee absolute security.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
                    <p>
                    Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete your personal information, and to
                    withdraw consent for communications. To exercise your rights, contact us at
                    <a href="mailto:tinytidestherapy@gmail.com" class="text-teal-600 underline">tinytidestherapy@gmail.com</a>.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
                    <p>
                    We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you believe
                    a child has provided us information, contact us and we will delete it promptly.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">9. Links to Other Websites</h2>
                    <p>
                    Our Site may contain links to other websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices. Please review
                    those policies before providing personal information.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="mb-10">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                    <p>
                    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we’ll post the updated version on this page with
                    a revised “Last updated” date.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-teal-500 mb-3">11. Contact Us</h2>
                    <p class="mb-2">If you have questions or privacy requests, please contact:</p>
                    <address class="not-italic text-gray-700">
                    <strong>Tiny Tides Therapy</strong><br />
                    Email:
                    <a href="mailto:tinytidestherapy@gmail.com" class="text-teal-600 underline">tinytidestherapy@gmail.com</a><br />
                    Jurisdiction: United States
                    </address>
                </section>
            </main>
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>